Interface AbstractObjectMetric<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the underlying type of the metric
All Known Subinterfaces:
AbstractObjectMetricSpace<T>, AbstractSearchableMetricSpace<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
EuclideanMetricSpace, ExplicitLandmarkSelector, ExplicitMetricSpace, GeometricSimplexStream, KDEuclideanMetricSpace, LandmarkSelector, MaxMinLandmarkSelector, ObjectSearchableFiniteMetricSpace, RandomLandmarkSelector, SkeletalMetric
public interface AbstractObjectMetric<T>

This interface defines a metric on the type T. Note that an implementing class should obey the axioms of a metric space - namely symmetry, positivity and the triangle inequality.

Author:
Andrew Tausz
